<image align="right" filename="harddrive.jpg" />

<blurb fontsize="3.6em">
Use the %hdparm% utility to maximize the performance of your harddrive.
</blurb>

<list>
	<bullet>%-c1% - set IDE 32-bit IO setting</bullet>
	<bullet>%-d1% - enable DMA</bullet>
	<bullet>%-u1% - enable IRQ unmasking</bullet> 
	<bullet>%-m16% - turn on multicount</bullet>
	<bullet>%-X 34|66|100% - transfer mode</bullet>
</list>

<blurb fontsize="3.6em">
Benchmark your drive via %hdparm -tT /dev/[drive]%
</blurb>

</slide>